ONE of the foremost celebrity cooking shows, Sokoyokoto, has returned after many years of hiatus. According to the producers, the show was rested to allow the producers to work assiduously behind the scenes for a bigger relaunch. The revamped celebrity cooking show now features two unique segments – the cooking segment and the chatting segment.   Braide Ifeanyi secures endorsement deal with House of…     Best Of Nollywood awards: Uzodinma to host 14th Edition     MI Abaga, Chigul, Waje join forces to advocate gender…   The celebrity cooking show returns with the backing of two corporate organisations, Flour Mills Nigeria Plc and Seven-Up Bottling Company Plc. While Flour Mills takes over the cooking segment, SevenUp bottling company takes charge of the chat segment. As is the tradition on Sokoyokoto, a rich array of stars from Nollywood, music and other spheres of Nigerian society have been invited to display culinary skills as well as party swag before a live audience.